tional Socialist politician himself that covers a period of over two decades. All diary entries are published in full version. Every entry is headed by a document summary listing the material on which the edition is based and briefly describing the record itself. A complete index in three volumes rounds off the edition and facilitates comprehensive searches for people, places and terms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aDierl, Florian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFröhlich, Elke, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHermann, Angela, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKeck, Ute, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aObermüller, Benjamin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSommersberg, Annika, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVollhardt, Ulla-Britta, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI0 cprintz978359821959740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311097247440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110972474423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110972474/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GHIc2000d2014